Fin scales:
pectoral and pelvic fins naked. Anal and dorsal fins variable: naked (
3
), two uniserial interradial scale series on soft dorsal fin base (
3
), two uniserial interradial scale series on soft dorsal fin base and soft anal fin base (
1
). Anterior third of caudal fin scaled, single series of minute cycloid scales on interradial membranes; scales in three anterior series much larger than posterior series.

Lower pharyngeal jaw plate: short and wide, length about 75 % of width (
Fig. 4
). Teeth in posterior row 21 , along midline 6 or 7 .
